The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Monday, December 29, 2003 				 Blaze in warfare school
 MUKHTAR AHMAD																								Srinagar, Dec. 28: A building housing several offices of the High Altitude Warfare School was gutted in a devastating blaze this morning.																								The cause of the fire that engulfed the entire bulding in Gulmarg is being ascertained, said defence public relations officer Col Mukhtar Singh. An inquiry has been ordered.																								Fire tenders were rushed to the spot to control the blaze in which six soldiers were injured. Sources said important equipment worth crores may have been destroyed.																								Singh said the warfare school, which teaches soldiers some of the toughest survival techniques while operating in extreme climate and inhospitable terrain, is one of the most high-profile training institutes of the Indian Army. 																								The school also boasts of the most sophisticated equipment and training facilities in South Asia. 
